#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code sliding window use karta hai maximum length nikalne ke liye
jisme at most k zeros ho sakte hain.

1. Do pointers liye hain:
   - l = window start
   - r = window end
2. Jaise-jaise r aage badhta hai, agar nums[r] = 0 ho to zeros count badha dete hain.
3. Agar zeros > k ho jaaye, to window invalid ho jaati hai,
   isliye left pointer ko aage badhate hain.
   Aur agar left par 0 tha to zeros count kam kar dete hain.
4. Jab tak zeros <= k hai, window valid hai,
   to uski length se maxLen update karte rehte hain.

Main idea:
Hume longest subarray chahiye jisme maximum k zeros ho,
kyuki unhi zeros ko flip karke saare 1 bana sakte hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int longestOnes(int[] nums, int k) {
        int l = 0;
        int r = 0;
        int maxLen = 0;
        int n = nums.length;
        int zeros = 0;

        while(r < n){
            if(nums[r] == 0) zeros++;

            if(zeros > k){
                if(nums[l] == 0) zeros--;
                l++;
            }

            if(zeros <= k){
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, r-l+1);
            }
            r++;
        }

        return maxLen;
    }
}
